name:                free-loops
version:             0.1.0.0
synopsis:            Fast imperative-style loops as a free monad EDSL
description:
  @free-loops@ is a library for fast, imperative-style loops in Haskell. The
  library is implemented as a free monad EDSL. @Do@-notation is used to
  construct nested loops, providing a cleaner syntax than manual recursion.
  Loops cannot allocate intermediate data structures so performance does not
  rely on stream fusion.
